      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The United Network for Organ Sharing is an organization focused on organ allocation policies and enhancing the efficiency of organ distribution to improve transplant outcomes."&lt;SEP&gt;"United Network for Organ Sharing (UNOS) is an organization responsible for overseeing the allocation of organs for transplantation in the United States, focusing on improving organ distribution efficiency and reducing waitlist deaths."&lt;SEP&gt;"United Network for Organ Sharing is an organization dedicated to optimizing organ allocation and reducing waitlist deaths through various distribution strategies."&lt;SEP&gt;"United Network for Organ Sharing is an organization focused on improving organ allocation efficiency, involving medical urgency and travel considerations to enhance transplant outcomes."</data>
