    <node id="&quot;RANSOMWARE ATTACK&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"A Ransomware Attack is a type of cyber incident where malicious software is used to block access to a system or data until a ransom is paid, referenced as a scenario where the Incident Response Team is activated."&lt;SEP&gt;"A ransomware attack involves cyber criminals demanding payment to restore access to data or systems, often characterized by escalating ransom demands and double extortion tactics."&lt;SEP&gt;"Ransomware Attack is a malicious event where the attacker demands payment to restore access to data or systems that have been compromised."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-2ab7db4d73efa5e36687c4d876434d5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08ddbccd90542cf4912ff8b8bf5900c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f23312381c9c1bbabf372b3b7a83e804</data>
    </node>
