      <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Attack kits and Malware as a Service are cybersecurity terms related to high-likelihood methods of conducting cyberattacks, showcased in the presentation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Attack kits and Malware as a Service refer to cyber attack tools available commercially, which are often low-cost and easily accessible for attackers."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-a7a5bd39de71e6cba00acabb57ae835d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8294a51b52c6428d0379eda99c59a329</data>
